High priority / ASAP:
- sessions support
- history browsing
- preferences dialog
- cookies manager
- transfers manager
- basic load progress indicator
- bookmarks

Medium priority / soon:
- custom searches
- proxy configuration
- private browsing
- mail and feeds client (as module)
- speed dial module
- detailed load progress information
- page preferences
- content blocking
- panels (page informations, notes, transfers, bookmarks etc.)
- multiple backend support (at least Blink with upcoming QtWebEngine)
- support for profiles / custom configuration directory
- system tray icon

Low priority / later:
- import of existing settings etc.
- delayed loading of Flash objects
- tabs pinning
- tabs grouping
- form auto completion
- passwords manager
- extensions
- Opera Link like solution
- improved integration with different platforms (Windows taskbar integration etc.)

Low priority / maybe:
- support for Opera skins (through custom QStyle)
- IM client module (libpurple based, including support for IRC)

And lots of smaller things. ;-)
